<down ref="RM000000XI9009X_04_0026" fin="false">OK</down>
<right ref="RM000000XI9009X_04_0017" fin="true">NG</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XI9009X_04_0026" proc-id="RM0250U___00007Y100000">
<testtitle>CHECK SPEED SENSOR AND SPEED SENSOR ROTOR SERRATIONS</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Reconnect the front speed sensor connector.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C136019E04" width="2.775699831in" height="4.7836529in"/>
</figure>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the oscilloscope to the front speed sensor terminal of the skid control ECU.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Check that a waveform is output when the tires are rotated.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>The same waveform is output from all the 4 wheels and there is no noise or interference in the waveform.</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>As the vehicle speed (wheel revolution speed) increases, a cycle of the waveform narrows and the output voltage becomes greater.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>When noise is identified in the waveform on the oscilloscope, the erratic signals are generated due to speed sensor rotor's scratches, looseness or foreign matter attached to it.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XI9009X_04_0011" fin="false">OK</down>
<right ref="RM000000XI9009X_04_0018" fin="true">NG</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XI9009X_04_0011" proc-id="RM0250U___00005LY00000">
